                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d691">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">762.9411/8: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-09-20T12:00:00+09:00"
                            >September 20, 1940—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received September 20—3:30
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>867. As a result of a 3-hour conference of the Emperor yesterday with the Cabinet
                    and the highest military and naval officials, I am informed from a reputable
                    source that the Emperor gave his sanction to the conclusion of a defensive
                    alliance with Germany. Details are not yet available but I shall explore.</p>
                <p>Sent to the Department. Repeated to Shanghai.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
